24:57.000 --> 25:00.630
<i>Unlike in the city where you have</i>
<i>Satanists running around.</i>

25:00.630 --> 25:04.210
<i>Well, you bring up a good question.</i>
<i>Is the Zodiac a Satanist?</i>

25:04.210 --> 25:06.000
<i>Amber from Oakland,</i>
<i>what do you think?</i>

25:06.000 --> 25:07.336
<i>I don't really know,</i>

25:07.336 --> 25:10.504
<i>but I thought that code</i>
<i>they printed didn't look very Christian.</i>

25:10.546 --> 25:13.336
<i>But I think the bigger problem</i>
<i>is that the papers shouldn't have printed</i>

25:13.336 --> 25:15.252
<i>anything that the Zodiac</i>
<i>has been doing.</i>

25:15.252 --> 25:18.504
<i>That they're just printing</i>
<i>all that stuff to sell more newspapers.</i>

25:18.504 --> 25:20.756
<i>Well, the Zodiac did demand</i>
<i>they print his letters</i>

25:20.756 --> 25:22.462
<i>or he'd kill more people.</i>

25:22.462 --> 25:23.882
<i>Yeah, but he would have</i>
<i>done it anyway,</i>

25:23.882 --> 25:25.546
<i>whether they printed it or not, I think.</i>

25:25.546 --> 25:27.084
<i>An interesting point.</i>

25:27.084 --> 25:29.252
<i>So, what do you think he'll do next?</i>

25:49.966 --> 25:53.420
<i>-San Francisco Police Department.</i>
<i>-Yes. There's a fight in a cab!</i>

25:53.420 --> 25:54.756
<i>What is your location?</i>

25:54.756 --> 25:57.840
<i>3398 Washington,</i>
<i>at the corner of Cherry.</i>

25:57.840 --> 25:59.672
<i>One's drunk and</i>
<i>we think he's robbing him.</i>

25:59.672 --> 26:03.042
<i>-Is the crime still in progress?</i>
<i>-Yes, please hurry.</i>

26:04.504 --> 26:06.126
Oh, my God, look!

26:29.000 --> 26:30.252
Nuts!

26:33.546 --> 26:35.462
Whoever this is,
you owe me a new lamp.

26:35.462 --> 26:38.168
<i>Cabbie's been shot</i>
<i>three blocks from the Presidio.</i>

26:38.168 --> 26:40.462
Well, it wasn't me.
I've been with my bride all night.

26:40.462 --> 26:43.546
-She can vouch.
-Go put on the Folgers.

26:43.546 --> 26:45.042
<i>You'll pick me up?</i>

26:45.042 --> 26:46.924
Let me just describe
the lamp you're gonna buy me.

26:55.714 --> 26:58.756
-I just got to sleep.
-Suspect's Negro, male adult.

26:58.756 --> 27:01.756
Walt's on scene, locked up the cab
and secured the crowd.

27:01.756 --> 27:04.378
Seriously, dead asleep.
I lost feeling in my arm and everything.

27:04.378 --> 27:05.714
Crackers.

27:09.546 --> 27:11.630
You ever try Japanese food?

27:11.630 --> 27:14.462
-What do you mean, like teriyaki?
-No, like the urchin.

27:14.462 --> 27:16.840
-Raw fish.
-I'm eating here, Bill.

27:18.168 --> 27:21.252
-I always wanted to try it.
-So, why don't you?

27:21.252 --> 27:23.252
Haven't got around to it.

27:38.840 --> 27:42.084
Evening, gents. What a lovely night
for a botched robbery.

27:42.084 --> 27:44.756
Yeah, third this week.
Must be end of summer rush.

27:44.756 --> 27:47.966
I got foot patrols going through the park,
dogs are on the way.

27:48.000 --> 27:52.378
The victim's name is Paul Stine.
Dousette pronounced him at 10:10.

27:52.378 --> 27:54.588
Suspect fired one shot
to the back of the head.

27:54.588 --> 27:56.588
Driver's wallet
and car keys are missing.

27:56.588 --> 27:57.714
How'd you know his name?

27:57.714 --> 28:00.756
Leroy, there, came down
from Yellow Cab to ID him.

28:00.756 --> 28:02.420
Neighborhood's pretty high-end
for this kind of thing,

28:02.420 --> 28:04.714
so I already set up transpo for the cab.

28:04.756 --> 28:06.294
-Coroner's here.
-Any witnesses?

28:06.294 --> 28:09.840
Kids who called it in
saw the suspect from that window.

28:09.840 --> 28:11.420
-Did they hear a shot?
-No.

28:11.420 --> 28:12.630
They first saw him in the front seat,

28:12.630 --> 28:14.630
thought he was a drunk
fighting with the driver.

28:14.630 --> 28:17.714
Oldest kid ran downstairs to get
a better look from the dining room,

28:17.714 --> 28:19.630
described him as a white male, glasses,

28:19.630 --> 28:21.924
crew-cut, stocky,
and wearing a dark jacket.

28:21.924 --> 28:23.840
Wait, I thought someone said
he was black.

28:23.840 --> 28:25.840
That's the description
that went out to radio cars.

28:25.840 --> 28:28.840
-We already corrected it.
-Oh, well, that's good.

28:28.840 --> 28:31.336
-You guys need anything else?
-No. Get out of here.

28:31.336 --> 28:33.378
Thanks. Happy Birthday.

28:33.378 --> 28:36.168
-Wait, it's your birthday?
-Yep.

28:36.168 --> 28:38.378
-That's great. Happy birthday.
-Thanks.

28:38.420 --> 28:41.504
-Body or scene?
-It's your birthday, I'll take the body.

28:41.504 --> 28:43.756
Dave, looks like he
wiped the cab down pretty good.

28:43.756 --> 28:46.252
-We got some blood over here.
-Prints?

28:46.252 --> 28:48.210
Could very well be.
We'll dust it at the Hall.

28:48.210 --> 28:51.042
The odd thing is, we also got gloves.

28:51.042 --> 28:53.462
-Suspect's?
-There's blood on them.

28:54.882 --> 28:56.168
-Hey, Pete?
-Yeah, Dave.

28:56.168 --> 28:57.462
You through over there,
can I get in there?

28:57.462 --> 28:59.126
Yeah, I'm all set.

29:00.042 --> 29:02.084
-Who rolled him?
-Stewarts.

29:08.966 --> 29:11.000
I got a single 9mm casing.

29:15.462 --> 29:16.882
Yeah, Luger.

29:17.420 --> 29:19.378
Nothing from the crowd.

29:19.378 --> 29:22.336
Okay.
I'm your shooter, Negro male adult,

29:22.336 --> 29:25.798
who also happens to be
a stocky, crew-cut Caucasian.

29:25.798 --> 29:28.420
I flag a cab. I give him this address.

29:28.420 --> 29:31.294
Did I give him this address?
Who's got the fare book?

29:31.294 --> 29:32.672
Right here.

29:34.966 --> 29:37.882
Washington and Maple.
That's one block east.

29:58.966 --> 30:00.210
Lighting's the same over here,

30:00.210 --> 30:02.756
so maybe I see
someone walking their dog.

30:02.756 --> 30:05.672
You don't want any witnesses
so you tell him to go down a block.

30:05.672 --> 30:06.840
He pulls over.

30:06.840 --> 30:08.882
I wait for him to put it in park
because I'm smart

30:08.882 --> 30:10.294
and I don't want him
hitting the accelerator

30:10.294 --> 30:11.672
when I shoot him. May I?

30:11.672 --> 30:14.126
He stops, puts it in park, boom.

30:14.126 --> 30:16.924
I shoot him on the right side,
he slumps right?

30:16.924 --> 30:19.042
Maybe you've got your hand
on his collar when you shoot.

30:19.042 --> 30:20.294
All right. So, either way,

30:20.294 --> 30:22.084
I just dumped a quart of blood
in the front seat.

30:22.084 --> 30:25.336
-So, why do you get in the front seat?
-For the money.

30:25.336 --> 30:26.462
But he's dead.

30:26.462 --> 30:28.294
You could just reach over the seat,
pull out his wallet.

30:28.294 --> 30:30.546
You don't have to go
anywhere near the blood.

30:30.546 --> 30:33.042
So, why'd he get in the front seat?

30:33.546 --> 30:35.252
-I'm an idiot.
-But you're not an idiot.

30:35.252 --> 30:37.084
You waited for him to put it in park.

30:37.084 --> 30:39.294
-Right. Thank you.
-Yeah, sure.

30:41.000 --> 30:42.882
-Can I see that?
-Yeah.

30:43.378 --> 30:46.756
I am an idiot.
I just killed a man for $8.25.

30:46.756 --> 30:51.084
It's his third fare of the night.
Does anyone have any animal crackers?

30:51.588 --> 30:53.924
-Animal crackers?
-They're in the car.

30:53.924 --> 30:56.210
I'm saving those for later.

30:56.210 --> 30:57.378
Fine.

31:01.840 --> 31:05.630
-Are you a reporter?
-No, I'm Inspector Dave Toschi, SFPD.

31:05.630 --> 31:08.294
Sir, I was wondering
if I'd be able to talk to your children,

31:08.294 --> 31:10.630
one at a time and preferably alone?

31:10.630 --> 31:13.000
They just saw a man murdered.

31:13.000 --> 31:14.126
I understand.

31:14.462 --> 31:16.210
It looked like
they were drunk and fighting.

31:16.210 --> 31:17.630
Yeah, and he had a rag.

31:17.630 --> 31:20.084
He came around the side of the car
and he was wiping stuff.

31:20.084 --> 31:23.546
-Did you get a chance to see his face?
-I did.

31:23.546 --> 31:25.042
Well, sort of.

31:26.336 --> 31:28.882
Did you remember what he looked like?

31:30.336 --> 31:32.420
-Normal.
-Yeah.

31:32.420 --> 31:33.756
"Normal?"

31:56.462 --> 31:58.126
<i>"This is the Zodiac speaking.</i>

31:58.126 --> 32:00.588
<i>"I am the murderer of the taxi driver</i>

32:00.588 --> 32:04.126
"over by Washington Street
and Maple Street last night.

32:04.126 --> 32:06.672
"To prove this, here is
a blood-stained piece of his shirt.

32:06.672 --> 32:11.714
"I am the same man who did in
the people in the North Bay Area.

32:11.714 --> 32:14.378
"The S.F. Police could have
caught him last night

32:14.378 --> 32:16.000
"if they had searched the park properly

32:16.000 --> 32:19.378
"instead of holding road races
with their motorcicles."

32:19.378 --> 32:21.000
-Gentlemen.
-Dave.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.966
Paul. Where's the shirt?

32:24.378 --> 32:26.042
Right there, boss.

32:27.168 --> 32:28.840
There's your rag the kids talked about.

32:28.840 --> 32:30.924
So he got in the front seat
to tear off a piece of the shirt.

32:30.924 --> 32:33.420
-Is this on the record?
-Well, what do you think?

32:33.420 --> 32:35.588
He confirms
the Vallejo and Napa killings.

32:35.588 --> 32:37.252
Gets worse.

32:37.252 --> 32:39.378
Robert, do you have a deadline?

32:39.378 --> 32:41.630
What does he mean, it gets worse?

32:41.630 --> 32:43.126
Read the last part.

32:43.126 --> 32:45.462
"School children make nice targets.

32:45.462 --> 32:47.840
"I think I shall wipe out
a school bus some morning.

32:47.840 --> 32:49.630
"Just shoot out the front tire

32:49.630 --> 32:52.126
"and then pick off the kiddies
as they come bouncing out."

32:52.126 --> 32:54.756
Jesus Christ, who's got school buses?
Department of Transportation?

32:54.756 --> 32:56.756
-School board.
-All right.

32:56.756 --> 32:59.126
I'm gonna need elimination prints
from your staff.

32:59.126 --> 33:01.882
Has anyone here
didn't touch this letter?

33:06.084 --> 33:08.378
On my way back to my desk.
They have phones, if you want.

33:08.378 --> 33:10.084
We need to get matches
on blood and fabric.

33:10.084 --> 33:11.336
I'll call Napa and Vallejo,

33:11.336 --> 33:13.252
get the letters up to Sherwood
in Sacramento.

33:13.252 --> 33:16.756
Dave, just one thing.
Is it true they got a print off the cab?

33:16.756 --> 33:19.126
Yeah, we got a partial in blood.

33:19.966 --> 33:23.168
-But that is not for publication.
-Hey, hey, come on.

33:23.168 --> 33:25.504
Hey, it's me.

33:25.504 --> 33:27.630
Did he say they got a print?

33:28.714 --> 33:29.966
Partial.

33:30.924 --> 33:32.000
Whoa.

33:33.378 --> 33:34.840
Dude, he wears his gun like Bullitt.

33:34.840 --> 33:37.420
No, McQueen got that from Toschi.

33:37.420 --> 33:39.294
Does he think that Zodiac's
gonna send another code?

33:39.294 --> 33:41.210
'Cause I think Zodiac's
gonna send another code.

33:41.210 --> 33:43.336
Jesus Harold Christ
on rubber crutches, Bobby.

33:43.336 --> 33:44.462
What are you doing?

33:44.462 --> 33:45.882
You're doing that thing,
the thing we discussed,

33:45.882 --> 33:48.462
the thing that I don't like.
Starts with an "L."

33:48.462 --> 33:50.462
-Oh, looming.
-Yeah.

33:50.462 --> 33:53.462
In cooperation with SFPD ,
we will run the Zodiac letter

33:53.462 --> 33:56.252
without including the threat
on school children.

33:56.252 --> 33:58.000
We don't want to start a city-wide panic

33:58.000 --> 34:01.630
so I'm asking all of you
to please keep this confidential.

34:01.630 --> 34:03.924
Just go about your daily business.

34:03.924 --> 34:05.294
Thank you.

34:20.966 --> 34:24.084
I packed you your carrots
and your soda and peanut butter, okay?

34:24.084 --> 34:27.084
-Dad, you don't have to wait with me.
-I know.

34:34.420 --> 34:38.252
You know what? You know what?
I'm gonna drive him today, okay?

34:38.714 --> 34:39.966
Come on.

34:57.966 --> 34:59.756
What's that?

34:59.756 --> 35:02.294
Similarities in the lowercase "r's."

35:11.462 --> 35:12.714
And that?

35:12.714 --> 35:14.756
It is you waiting in the hall
if you speak again.

35:14.756 --> 35:16.630
I have to concentrate.

35:17.000 --> 35:18.210
Sorry.

35:18.210 --> 35:20.378
"Sorry" counts as speaking.

35:31.084 --> 35:34.084
There are similarities
in the lowercase "r's."

35:38.126 --> 35:40.588
We have to release the bus threat.

35:41.168 --> 35:43.882
-It'll screw us.
-We're already screwed.

35:43.882 --> 35:46.210
We just went from
"Routine Cabbie Shooting"

35:46.210 --> 35:48.420
to "Mass Murderer Targets Kids."

35:56.210 --> 35:59.378
<i>The Zodiac Killer</i>
<i>has come to San Francisco.</i>

35:59.378 --> 36:00.462
<i>Confirmation tonight,</i>

36:00.462 --> 36:02.504
<i>from the San Francisco</i>
<i>Police Department</i>

36:02.504 --> 36:04.546
<i>that in his latest haunting letter,</i>

36:04.546 --> 36:07.840
<i>which takes credit for the murder</i>
<i>of cab driver Paul Stine,</i>

36:07.840 --> 36:11.336
<i>the Zodiac has threatened to,</i>
<i>"Wipe out a school bus</i>

36:11.336 --> 36:14.672
<i>"and pick off the kiddies</i>
<i>as they come bouncing out."</i>

36:18.126 --> 36:20.882
<i>If you think you might know</i>
<i>who the Zodiac is,</i>

36:20.882 --> 36:25.042
<i>you can call the San Francisco</i>
<i>Police Department's newest tip line.</i>

36:48.168 --> 36:51.546
Press conference is at 4:00.
We got to give them something.

36:51.546 --> 36:53.042
We're coordinating
with the school board,

36:53.042 --> 36:55.042
and we expect
a break in the case very soon.

36:55.042 --> 36:56.882
-What do we really got?
-We're swamped.

36:56.882 --> 36:58.378
When they can't get anyone
on the tip line

36:58.378 --> 37:00.168
they call the switchboard
and keep getting put through.

37:00.168 --> 37:01.252
You got any hard suspects?

37:01.252 --> 37:04.084
About 90 an hour. I'm up to around 500.

37:04.084 --> 37:05.294
Well, can't you narrow it down?

37:05.294 --> 37:07.546
I would love to,
if I could get out of this...

37:07.546 --> 37:11.126
-Homicide, please hold.
-Yeah, hold, please.

37:11.126 --> 37:12.966
We're gonna need to tell them
we got the entire force on this.

37:12.966 --> 37:14.336
How many men can you give me?

37:14.336 --> 37:16.462
Well, right now, it's you and Bill
and Monday's a school day.

37:16.462 --> 37:18.462
Yeah, I know, Chief.
I have three daughters of my own.

37:18.462 --> 37:20.504
Yeah, I know. Where's Armstrong?

37:20.504 --> 37:22.042
He's on the phone with Vallejo.

37:22.042 --> 37:24.084
We're playing catch up, Jack.

37:24.084 --> 37:26.714
I'd like to set up a meeting
with your survivor, Michael Mageau.

37:26.714 --> 37:28.378
I can't. He skipped town.

37:28.378 --> 37:31.126
The only guy who's seen Zodiac
without a mask is missing?

37:31.126 --> 37:34.378
When he was still in the hospital
we could show him lineups all day long.

37:34.378 --> 37:35.882
As soon as he got out, he split.

37:35.882 --> 37:37.000
<i>Really? Why?</i>

37:37.000 --> 37:39.294
I don't think he wanted
to have anything to do with this.

37:39.294 --> 37:41.588
<i>Can you send us everything</i>
<i>that you have?</i>

37:41.588 --> 37:44.420
Well, the road goes both ways.

37:44.420 --> 37:47.630
Now, we need that print
you lifted from the cab

37:47.630 --> 37:49.672
<i>and we should have been in</i>
<i>on the handwriting.</i>

37:49.672 --> 37:52.042
I apologize.
Things have been moving fast.

37:52.042 --> 37:54.882
<i>Who should I talk to in Napa</i>
<i>so we can coordinate?</i>

37:54.882 --> 37:56.126
Talk to Ken Narlow.

37:56.126 --> 37:58.084
We really should have been in
on the handwriting.

37:58.084 --> 38:00.672
<i>I apologize.</i>
<i>Things have been moving fast.</i>

38:00.672 --> 38:02.210
<i>Listen, we're gonna need</i>
<i>your scene photos.</i>

38:02.210 --> 38:03.336
Can't help you.

38:03.336 --> 38:05.378
<i>Ken, I don't want to get into</i>
<i>a jurisdictional thing here.</i>

38:05.378 --> 38:08.084
No, no, no, no, no.
We didn't have a crime scene.

38:08.084 --> 38:11.420
The ranger that found the kids literally
swept everything into a picnic blanket.

38:11.420 --> 38:13.210
<i>All we have are the Wing Walker prints.</i>

38:13.210 --> 38:14.420
The what?

38:14.420 --> 38:16.210
Boot prints to and from the crime scene

38:16.210 --> 38:17.966
were made by size
10-and-a-half Wing Walkers,

38:17.966 --> 38:21.420
military-style boots
sold only at military PXs

38:21.882 --> 38:23.798
designed to walk
on the wings of planes.

38:23.798 --> 38:26.630
<i>And you can't buy at a PX</i>
<i>without a military ID,</i>

38:26.630 --> 38:28.672
so our suspect could be military.

38:28.672 --> 38:30.504
Did you guys narrow your list off of this?

38:30.546 --> 38:32.714
-Yeah.
<i>-Did Vallejo?</i>

38:32.714 --> 38:34.924
I don't know. I don't work in Vallejo.
I work here.

38:34.924 --> 38:37.168
Great. I'm gonna need photos
of those boot prints.

38:37.168 --> 38:39.210
<i>Sure, if you send me the handwriting.</i>

38:39.252 --> 38:40.924
I thought Questioned Documents
already did.

38:40.924 --> 38:42.546
Nope. Vallejo's got them, not us.

38:42.546 --> 38:44.630
All right.
I'll have Questioned Documents...

38:44.630 --> 38:46.630
Forget it. I'll telefax it to you.

38:46.630 --> 38:48.210
We don't have telefax yet.

38:48.210 --> 38:50.924
-Okay, I'll put it in the mail.
<i>-We'll mail ours, too.</i>

38:50.924 --> 38:52.672
And call Mulanax in Vallejo.

38:52.672 --> 38:54.882
-Maybe he can get you a mimeo.
-Right.

38:54.882 --> 38:57.336
Why don't you just get a photo
off the original plaster cast?

38:57.336 --> 38:59.546
We'd have to wait,
because they don't have a fax.

38:59.546 --> 39:01.084
<i>We don't have a fax, either.</i>

39:01.084 --> 39:02.924
Look, I'm just trying
to get us coordinated.

39:02.924 --> 39:04.504
Have you called Solano Sheriff's Office?

39:04.504 --> 39:06.210
Why would I call Solano?

39:06.210 --> 39:09.924
<i>Because the two kids that got killed</i>
<i>last Christmas were Solano's.</i>

39:09.924 --> 39:11.210
I thought they were Vallejo.

39:11.210 --> 39:12.630
No, they were over the county line

39:12.630 --> 39:14.924
so you're gonna need
to coordinate with them, too.

39:14.924 --> 39:16.462
Okay.

39:16.462 --> 39:17.588
Bill.

39:18.252 --> 39:20.168
Can I have a word with you?

39:23.084 --> 39:25.210
Where did you see this guy?

39:25.966 --> 39:28.504
We got the call to circle the scene
and look for a Negro male adult.

39:28.504 --> 39:30.084
Where was he?

39:30.084 --> 39:32.630
On Jackson. Heading east.
About the middle of the block.

39:32.630 --> 39:34.756
And this is three minutes
after the shooting?

39:34.756 --> 39:36.000
Give or take. Yeah.

39:36.000 --> 39:38.378
-And you were heading east or west?
-We were going west.

39:38.378 --> 39:40.714
All right, so you're
on Jackson going west.

39:40.714 --> 39:43.924
So the cab was one block
catty-corner southwest?

39:43.924 --> 39:45.714
-Correct.
-Did you slow down?

39:45.714 --> 39:47.546
-Of course we slowed down.
-All right.

39:47.546 --> 39:49.882
Listen, Dispatch said
it was a Negro male.

39:49.882 --> 39:51.252
That was corrected.

39:51.252 --> 39:54.000
No, but at the time
they hadn't changed it.

39:54.000 --> 39:56.168
This guy was white.

39:56.168 --> 39:58.126
Right, not in a hurry.
Kind of lumbering along like...

39:58.126 --> 40:00.966
Lumbering?
What do you mean, "lumbering"?

40:02.000 --> 40:04.756
-Shuffling.
-Stocky? Had a crew cut?

40:05.672 --> 40:08.000
Yeah, that's all correct.

40:08.000 --> 40:09.798
Listen, it was dark.

40:10.672 --> 40:12.840
The guy was wearing a dark jacket.
There's no way...

40:12.840 --> 40:15.336
He would have been covered in blood.

40:16.924 --> 40:18.546
Did you stop him?

40:20.588 --> 40:22.378
Did you talk to him?

40:22.966 --> 40:24.924
-Yes? No?
-No.

40:25.798 --> 40:27.420
You need to get with a sketch artist.

40:27.420 --> 40:30.420
We have to put out
a new composite right away.

40:33.504 --> 40:36.546
<i>Five persons have been murdered</i>
<i>in the San Francisco area,</i>

40:36.546 --> 40:38.042
<i>and in each case the killer...</i>

40:38.042 --> 40:40.672
<i>"I shall wipe out a school bus</i>
<i>some morning..."</i>

40:40.672 --> 40:42.294
<i>San Francisco police...</i>

40:44.168 --> 40:46.714
<i>...to see the Stones in concert</i>
<i>this Sunday.</i>

40:47.000 --> 40:49.168
<i>The new letters</i>
<i>from the Zodiac Killer were sent to</i>

40:49.168 --> 40:51.294
<i>the City room of the</i>
San Francisco Chronicle.

40:51.294 --> 40:52.546
<i>One of the letters was...</i>

40:52.546 --> 40:55.210
Looming. No looming.

40:55.210 --> 40:58.420
-Have you considered the water theory?
-What?

40:58.420 --> 41:01.336
Geographically, every attack
takes place near a body of water

41:01.336 --> 41:02.588
-or a water-based name.
-This is your water theory?

41:02.588 --> 41:05.126
Lake Berryessa. Blue Rock Springs.

41:05.126 --> 41:07.798
-Lake Herman.
-Wash-ington and Cherry?

41:09.252 --> 41:10.966
You think?

41:10.966 --> 41:12.084
No.

41:12.084 --> 41:13.588
I'm reading this book,

41:13.588 --> 41:15.336
<i>Homicide Investigation</i>
by Lemoyne Snyder...

41:15.336 --> 41:16.840
-"Leymone."
-...and he says you look for patterns,

41:16.840 --> 41:19.042
-so I'm looking for patterns.
-No.

41:19.042 --> 41:21.462
You can't think of this case
in normal police terms.

41:21.462 --> 41:23.714
-Why not?
-You got four crime scenes.

41:23.714 --> 41:26.756
Solano, Vallejo, Berryessa, and here.

41:26.756 --> 41:30.462
Not a single usable print
at the first three or in any of the letters?

41:30.924 --> 41:34.462
How does our master criminal come
to the city and leave a bloody latent?

41:34.462 --> 41:37.126
I mean, assuming the gloves are his,

41:37.126 --> 41:38.966
he shoots the cabbie
and then takes them off?

41:38.966 --> 41:40.210
<i>So it's not his print?</i>

41:40.210 --> 41:42.084
Maybe, maybe not.
You're missing the point.

41:42.084 --> 41:44.798
-The point is the first attack...
-David Faraday and Betty Jensen.

41:44.798 --> 41:46.462
They both die.

41:46.462 --> 41:49.000
From there on out,
he only manages to kill the girls.

41:49.000 --> 41:51.042
-Not for lack of trying.
-Not for lack of trying.

41:51.042 --> 41:54.714
Mageau lives, Ferrin dies.
Hartnell lives, Shepard dies.

41:54.714 --> 41:58.168
He gets so caught up with the women
he forgets to finish off the men.

41:58.168 --> 42:00.588
Plus, they're all couples
and all on lover's lanes.

42:00.588 --> 42:02.546
-Paul Stine is not.
-Exactly.

42:02.546 --> 42:04.840
Single, male cab driver
on Washington and Cherry doesn't fit.

42:04.840 --> 42:06.252
Doesn't fit.

42:07.126 --> 42:09.420
So, why does Zodiac kill him?

42:12.210 --> 42:14.252
He's breaking the pattern.

42:23.420 --> 42:24.546
Yeah?

42:24.546 --> 42:28.378
<i>Someone claiming to be Zodiac</i>
<i>called Oakland PD a half-hour ago.</i>

42:28.378 --> 42:31.714
<i>He says he's gonna call in on Jim</i>
<i>Dunbar's morning show in three hours.</i>

42:31.714 --> 42:32.882
On television?

42:32.924 --> 42:35.084
<i>He wants Melvin Belli on</i>
<i>to counsel him.</i>

42:35.084 --> 42:37.210
All right. All right.
Let's go wake up Melvin.

42:39.630 --> 42:41.630
Animal crackers?

42:41.630 --> 42:43.000
Glove box.

42:43.000 --> 42:44.798
Are these windows bulletproof?

42:44.798 --> 42:47.462
Yes, Melvin.
You don't have to lie down back there.

42:47.462 --> 42:48.756
This man is a marksman,

42:48.756 --> 42:51.672
could snuff me out
at a moment's notice.

42:51.672 --> 42:53.168
Are you sure you're up for this?

42:53.168 --> 42:57.672
Don't you worry about me, Inspector.
I'll be fine when the lights are on.

42:57.672 --> 42:59.546
This man has asked for my help.

42:59.546 --> 43:01.714
The man you're worrying about
snuffing you out?

43:01.714 --> 43:03.672
What are these, cookies?

43:05.336 --> 43:07.462
Dear Lord, do you ever clean this car?

43:07.756 --> 43:11.210
-Shit.
-KGO must have tipped other stations.

43:20.756 --> 43:23.798
<i>Get him talking.</i>
<i>Convince him to meet you somewhere.</i>

43:23.798 --> 43:25.168
If you see an opportunity,

43:25.168 --> 43:28.000
we want you to suggest
Old St. Mary's Church in Chinatown.

43:28.000 --> 43:29.294
You'll be tracing the call?

43:29.294 --> 43:32.504
Pacific Telephone says you need to
keep him on the line for 15 minutes.

43:32.504 --> 43:34.756
We can do that, can't we, Jim?

43:37.084 --> 43:39.462
Fifteen seconds. Clear the set.

43:45.798 --> 43:48.126
Here you go, you drunken reprobate.

43:48.126 --> 43:52.000
<i>We interrupt our regular program</i>
<i>to bring you this news bulletin.</i>

43:52.000 --> 43:54.084
<i>Welcome to this special edition</i>
<i>of our show</i>

43:54.084 --> 43:56.042
<i>in which we are joined</i>
<i>by attorney Melvin Belli</i>

43:56.042 --> 43:59.504
<i>who the Zodiac Killer</i>
<i>personally requested to appear.</i>

43:59.504 --> 44:01.462
Finish up, buddy, and put it in the sink.

44:01.462 --> 44:04.546
<i>-Good morning, Melvin.</i>
<i>-Good morning, Jim.</i>

44:04.546 --> 44:07.882
<i>So, the phone lines are open.</i>
<i>Mr. Belli is here.</i>

44:07.882 --> 44:09.042
<i>Here to help, Jim.</i>

44:09.042 --> 44:10.966
<i>Yes. Here to help.</i>

44:10.966 --> 44:15.714
<i>And we ask the public not to call in,</i>
<i>so that the Zodiac himself can reach us.</i>

44:24.756 --> 44:28.252
I saw your Star Trek, by the way.
It was excellent.

44:28.252 --> 44:30.294
A shame about the show.

44:30.294 --> 44:31.840
Good people.

44:31.840 --> 44:35.672
You know, I've often thought of
becoming an actor full-time.

44:35.672 --> 44:37.042
What was your character's name?

44:37.042 --> 44:39.294
<i>-Gorgon.</i>
<i>-Gorgon. That's right.</i>

44:40.798 --> 44:42.798
Roll the tape. Get the tape.

44:42.798 --> 44:45.462
Jim, we have a call. We're going live.

44:46.714 --> 44:47.924
Hello?

44:51.420 --> 44:53.630
Hello? This is Melvin Belli.

44:54.798 --> 44:56.966
Who am I speaking with?

44:56.966 --> 44:59.378
<i>This is the Zodiac speaking.</i>

45:02.504 --> 45:06.378
Is there something I can call you
that's a little less ominous?

45:08.336 --> 45:09.420
<i>Sam.</i>

45:10.000 --> 45:11.966
Sam.

45:12.294 --> 45:15.966
Is there somewhere we can meet, Sam,
and talk about this?

45:16.378 --> 45:19.714
<i>Meet me on top of the Fairmont Hotel.</i>

45:19.756 --> 45:21.588
<i>Without anyone else or I’ll jump...</i>

45:21.588 --> 45:23.504
Have a unit go to the Fairmont Hotel.

45:23.504 --> 45:25.756
<i>-Sam.</i>
-Yes?

45:26.420 --> 45:29.966
Do you think you need medical care?

45:29.966 --> 45:31.966
<i>Medical, not mental.</i>

45:31.966 --> 45:34.336
Do you have health problems?

45:34.336 --> 45:36.168
<i>I’m sick. I have headaches.</i>

45:36.168 --> 45:38.000
Headaches?

45:38.000 --> 45:39.462
I have headaches, too,

45:39.462 --> 45:42.252
but a chiropractor stopped them
a week ago.

45:42.252 --> 45:44.084
I think I can help you, Sam.

45:46.504 --> 45:47.798
Sam?

45:49.714 --> 45:52.168
He knows they're tracing his calls.

45:55.840 --> 45:59.966
<i>Sam, we'd like you to know</i>
<i>that we are not tracing these calls.</i>

45:59.966 --> 46:04.252
<i>It's a long, difficult process</i>
<i>and ineffective with these short calls.</i>

46:09.714 --> 46:10.798
Sam?

46:13.042 --> 46:16.168
We're not tracing these calls.
You have my word.

46:17.042 --> 46:18.252
<i>Okay.</i>

46:18.714 --> 46:22.084
<i>Sam, you need to tell me</i>
<i>what your problem is.</i>

46:22.084 --> 46:24.042
<i>I don't want to go to the gas chamber.</i>

46:24.042 --> 46:26.672
<i>I have headaches.</i>
<i>I kill, I don't get them.</i>

46:26.672 --> 46:28.084
That is fucked up!

46:28.084 --> 46:31.672
<i>You want to live, don't you?</i>
<i>Well, this is your passport.</i>

46:31.672 --> 46:33.168
<i>How long have you been</i>
<i>having these headaches?</i>

46:33.168 --> 46:35.210
<i>Since I killed a kid.</i>

46:36.126 --> 46:38.462
-Do you have blackouts?
<i>-Yes.</i>

46:38.462 --> 46:42.294
-Do you have fits?
<i>-No. I just have headaches.</i>

46:42.294 --> 46:44.000
Did you attempt to call one other time

46:44.000 --> 46:46.672
when F. Lee Bailey was with us
two or three weeks ago?

46:46.672 --> 46:47.798
<i>Yes.</i>

46:47.798 --> 46:49.714
And why did you want
to talk to Mr. Bailey?

46:49.714 --> 46:52.756
Why do you wanna tal k to me, Sam?

46:52.756 --> 46:54.504
<i>-I don't want to be hurt.</i>
-Why is he calling?

46:54.504 --> 46:56.546
-Hey, just a second, buddy.
<i>-I don't wanna go to the gas chamber.</i>

46:56.546 --> 46:58.336
<i>You won't get hurt if you talk to me.</i>

46:58.336 --> 47:01.420
And you're not going
to the gas chamber.

47:01.420 --> 47:03.924
I wouldn't think they would ask
for capital punishment.

47:03.924 --> 47:06.168
<i>We should ask the District Attorney.</i>

47:06.168 --> 47:08.336
<i>Do you want me to do that, Sam?</i>

47:08.336 --> 47:11.084
<i>Do you want me to talk</i>
<i>to the District Attorney?</i>

47:14.966 --> 47:16.714
What was that, Sam?

47:17.672 --> 47:19.840
<i>I did not say anything.</i>

47:19.840 --> 47:21.798
<i>We heard a scream.</i>

47:22.546 --> 47:24.714
<i>That was my headache.</i>

47:25.504 --> 47:28.504
You sound like you're in
a great deal of pain.

47:29.210 --> 47:32.294
<i>My head aches. I’m so sick.</i>

47:34.126 --> 47:35.756
<i>I’m gonna kill them.</i>

47:35.756 --> 47:38.672
-Oh, okay.
<i>-I’m gonna kill those kids!</i>

47:38.672 --> 47:40.294
Fantastic.

47:42.840 --> 47:44.294
<i>Sam?</i>

47:45.798 --> 47:50.126
<i>-Let's meet and talk. Just us.</i>
<i>-Okay.</i>

47:50.168 --> 47:52.924
<i>How about Old St. Mary's Church</i>
<i>in Chinatown?</i>

47:52.924 --> 47:54.336
<i>No.</i>

47:54.336 --> 47:58.294
<i>In front of the Daly City</i>
<i>St. Vincent de Paul at 10:30.</i>

47:58.294 --> 48:00.042
I'll see you there.

48:01.798 --> 48:03.756
Take care of yourself, Sam.

48:28.042 --> 48:29.336
My, my, my.

48:29.336 --> 48:33.084
You fellows certainly know
how to put on a secret meeting.

48:35.420 --> 48:37.042
<i>You know, the problem is,</i>

48:37.042 --> 48:39.966
<i>I don't want to go to the gas chamber.</i>
<i>I have headaches.</i>

48:39.966 --> 48:42.084
<i>I kill, I don't get them.</i>

48:42.084 --> 48:43.756
No, it's not him.

48:44.798 --> 48:48.042
It's the voice.
The voice is too high. It's too young.

48:48.042 --> 48:50.378
All right.
Thanks for coming down, Bryan.

48:50.378 --> 48:51.756
<i>Do you have blackouts?</i>

48:51.756 --> 48:53.630
That's okay. I got it.

48:59.798 --> 49:00.924
They pulled off the trace.

49:00.924 --> 49:04.294
Our Daly City no-show
called from a mental institution.

49:04.294 --> 49:06.252
Oakland PD's operator is sure

49:06.252 --> 49:08.840
the man she talked to
had a deeper voice.

49:08.840 --> 49:10.000
Calmer.

49:10.840 --> 49:13.042
Might have actually been him.

49:19.336 --> 49:22.630
"So I shall change
my way of collecting slaves.

49:22.630 --> 49:26.210
"I shall no longer announce to anyone
when I commit my murders.

49:26.210 --> 49:29.504
"They shall look like routine robberies,
killings of anger

49:29.504 --> 49:32.588
"and a few fake accidents, et cetera.

49:32.588 --> 49:33.756
"The police shall never catch me

49:33.756 --> 49:36.252
"because I have been
too clever for them.

49:36.252 --> 49:39.882
"I look like the description passed out
only when I do my thing.

49:39.882 --> 49:43.042
"The rest of the time
I look entirely different.

49:43.042 --> 49:47.546
"I shall not tell you what
my disguise consists of when I kill.

49:48.126 --> 49:50.756
"As of yet I have left no
fingerprints behind me,

49:50.756 --> 49:53.378
"contrary to what the police say.

49:53.378 --> 49:55.756
"I wear transparent fingertips.

49:56.714 --> 50:01.546
"All it is is two coats of airplane cement
coated on my fingertips.

50:01.546 --> 50:06.126
"I enjoy needling the blue pigs.
Hey, blue pig, I was in the park.

50:06.126 --> 50:11.672
"You were using fire trucks to mask
the sound of your cruising prowl cars.

50:11.714 --> 50:13.210
"Hey, pig, doesn't it rile you up

50:13.210 --> 50:16.420
"to have your nose
rubbed in your booboos?

50:16.420 --> 50:19.588
"If you cops think I am going to take
on a bus the way I stated I was,

50:19.588 --> 50:22.840
"you deserve to have holes
in your heads."

50:24.756 --> 50:26.966
And you need to look at this.

50:29.798 --> 50:32.294
"Take one bag of
ammonium nitrate fertilizer,

50:32.294 --> 50:34.042
"one gallon of stove oil,

50:34.042 --> 50:36.294
"and dump a few bags
of gravel on top..."

50:36.294 --> 50:38.126
-Okay.
-It's a bomb.

50:38.126 --> 50:40.000
Okay. We gotta call the Army
and see if this

50:40.000 --> 50:42.840
science experiment could actually work.

50:42.840 --> 50:44.378
Another cipher.

50:46.588 --> 50:49.378
-When did these arrive?
-They arrived this morning.

50:49.378 --> 50:50.882
Are you planning to publish?

50:50.882 --> 50:52.084
Robert.

50:53.588 --> 50:55.546
We should have a drink.

50:59.672 --> 51:01.084
Thank you.

51:02.882 --> 51:05.210
So, tell me about yourself.

51:05.210 --> 51:08.756
-You married?
-Divorced. Two kids.

51:09.756 --> 51:11.672
What do you do for fun?

51:13.168 --> 51:14.798
I love to read.

51:15.714 --> 51:18.294
-I enjoy books.
-Those are the same things.

51:18.294 --> 51:20.840
Why you been going through my trash?

51:23.672 --> 51:25.546
I'll come back to that.

51:26.042 --> 51:27.840
How did you know
he was gonna send another code?

51:27.840 --> 51:29.672
I just guessed.

51:29.672 --> 51:31.924
-Just guessed.
-The first one seemed too easy.

51:31.924 --> 51:34.378
All right, this can no longer be ignored.

51:34.378 --> 51:38.084
-What is that you're drinking?
-It's an Aqua Velva.

51:38.084 --> 51:41.000
You wouldn't make fun of it
if you tried it.

51:50.504 --> 51:52.924
But who actually cracked the code?

51:53.714 --> 51:56.042
A married couple who like puzzles.

51:56.042 --> 51:58.294
So what's that tell us about the Zodiac?

51:58.294 --> 51:59.714
-He's no expert.
-Right.

51:59.714 --> 52:01.462
It's just a simple substitution code

52:01.462 --> 52:03.756
like the one that
we used to do as boy scouts.

52:03.756 --> 52:05.504
"A" is one, "B" is two.

52:05.504 --> 52:06.924
We weren't all boy scouts, Robert.

52:06.924 --> 52:10.588
Well, it's not that hard.
You just got to know where to start.

52:10.588 --> 52:12.462
In the first cipher...

52:12.462 --> 52:13.798
You actually carry that around with you?

52:13.798 --> 52:15.504
-Why?
-No reason.

52:16.630 --> 52:20.168
What's the most common double
consonant in the English language?

52:20.168 --> 52:21.336
Consonant?

52:21.336 --> 52:22.756
-The double "L."
-Double "L."

52:22.756 --> 52:26.714
And what's the one word that we know
that he'll use in here, at least once?

52:26.714 --> 52:27.882
-"Kill."
-Right, "kill."

52:27.882 --> 52:29.420
So the Hardens start looking
for double symbols,

52:29.420 --> 52:31.504
which they find here, here, and here.

52:31.504 --> 52:34.042
Each with the same
two symbols preceding them.

52:34.042 --> 52:36.084
So now they've got
a repeating four-letter word

52:36.084 --> 52:38.210
ending with two symbols
that they assume stand for "L."

52:38.210 --> 52:39.756
And since they think the whole word
is "kill" then...

52:39.756 --> 52:43.210
Then you got your "K," you got your "I,"
and you're on your way.

52:43.210 --> 52:45.168
But how do you go
from "A" is one and "B" is two

52:45.168 --> 52:46.630
to figuring out this whole code?

52:46.630 --> 52:49.546
Well, same way I did.
You go to the library.

52:52.840 --> 52:54.840
In this book,

52:54.840 --> 52:59.042
the author presents a very simple
substitution code in the preface.

52:59.042 --> 53:02.084
Eight of the 26 symbols that
he suggests are found in this cipher.

53:02.084 --> 53:03.462
Yeah, but there are non-letter symbols

53:03.462 --> 53:04.966
because there's all
these medieval ones.

53:04.966 --> 53:07.546
I thought they looked medieval, too.

53:08.420 --> 53:10.294
But then I found a code
written in the Middle Ages.

53:10.294 --> 53:11.378
Guess what it's called?

53:12.126 --> 53:13.924
The Zodiac Alphabet.

53:15.882 --> 53:17.084
Jesus.

53:18.252 --> 53:19.798
What do you want out of this?

53:19.798 --> 53:21.378
-What?
-What's your angle?

53:21.378 --> 53:24.252
This is good business
for everyone but you.

53:27.378 --> 53:29.168
How do you mean "business"?

53:32.210 --> 53:34.672
Hey. Come to bed.

53:34.672 --> 53:37.966
I'll be up in a minute.
I need to make a phone call.

53:49.546 --> 53:51.252
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Bill?

53:52.084 --> 53:54.546
There's not many basements
in California.

53:54.546 --> 53:56.798
<i>"Basement for future use."</i>

53:56.840 --> 53:58.420
That's right.

53:58.420 --> 54:02.168
<i>I’ll have Vallejo and Napa</i>
<i>check with their city planners.</i>

54:02.168 --> 54:04.378
<i>-Get some sleep.</i>
-Yeah, sure.

54:17.294 --> 54:20.252
<i>"Dear Melvin,</i>
<i>this is the Zodiac speaking.</i>

54:20.252 --> 54:22.504
<i>"I wish you a happy Christmas.</i>

54:22.504 --> 54:26.042
<i>"The one thing I ask of you is this.</i>
<i>Please help me.</i>

54:26.042 --> 54:29.546
"I cannot reach out for help
because this thing in me won't let me."

54:29.546 --> 54:31.000
Thank you.

54:31.000 --> 54:34.294
"I am finding it extremely difficult
to hold it in check

54:34.294 --> 54:37.000
"and I am afraid I will lose control again

54:37.000 --> 54:39.924
"and take my ninth
and possibly tenth victim."

54:39.924 --> 54:42.336
Melvin, he's reaching out to you.

54:42.336 --> 54:43.756
Absolutely.

54:43.756 --> 54:47.378
Inspectors, he sent this letter
directly to my residence.

54:47.420 --> 54:50.546
It is a cry for help,
intended as a private communiqué.

54:50.546 --> 54:52.756
Which is why
you contacted the Chronicle.

54:52.756 --> 54:55.882
The people have a right to know.
Toddy?

54:55.882 --> 54:59.042
-When did the letter arrive?
-In the middle of last week.

54:59.042 --> 55:01.546
I was away on safari.

55:01.546 --> 55:03.420
What did you gentlemen
do for Christmas?

55:03.420 --> 55:05.840
-You're looking at it.
-You must see Africa.

55:05.840 --> 55:11.126
Cradle of civilization.
Fascinating people. Beautiful. Savage.

55:11.126 --> 55:15.000
-Back to the killer who wrote to you.
-Yes. Of course.

55:15.000 --> 55:17.000
It is my belief
that he only penned this letter

55:17.000 --> 55:20.126
because he couldn't get through to me
on the Dunbar show or here.

55:20.126 --> 55:22.756
-He tried to contact you here?
-Several times.

55:22.756 --> 55:25.000
