1:12:56.210 --> 1:12:57.882
<i>Enjoy your flight.</i>

1:13:01.714 --> 1:13:03.882
-Cross? Hi.
-Yeah.

1:13:03.882 --> 1:13:06.252
-Detective David Toschi, SFPD.
-How are you doing?

1:13:06.252 --> 1:13:07.882
Great. Thanks for having us
down today.

1:13:07.882 --> 1:13:10.462
Not at all.
I hear you have some files for us.

1:13:10.462 --> 1:13:12.084
I'll show you mine. You show me yours.

1:13:12.084 --> 1:13:14.462
-Frisco huh?
-That's right. San Francisco.

1:13:15.084 --> 1:13:16.630
-Ken Narlow from Napa.
-Ken.

1:13:16.630 --> 1:13:18.462
-Mel Nicolai, Justice.
-Mel.

1:13:18.462 --> 1:13:19.504
Here's what we know.

1:13:19.504 --> 1:13:22.168
Cheri Jo Bates attended
Riverside Community College.

1:13:22.168 --> 1:13:26.588
She studies in the library
the night of October 30th, 1966.

1:13:26.588 --> 1:13:30.504
She leaves with an unidentified male
at closing, 9:00 p.m.

1:13:30.504 --> 1:13:34.294
Her body's found the next morning
in a parking lot, stabbed to death.

1:13:34.294 --> 1:13:35.714
Her car is disabled.

1:13:35.714 --> 1:13:38.756
Someone cut the coil in the distributor,
the battery died.

1:13:38.756 --> 1:13:41.252
The someone comes back,
offers to help.

1:13:41.252 --> 1:13:43.504
-Like Kathleen Johns.
-Who?

1:13:43.504 --> 1:13:46.252
A woman outside of Modesto,
might be a Zodiac victim.

1:13:46.252 --> 1:13:49.882
Might. Might be.
I have her comp right here in this file.

1:13:49.882 --> 1:13:51.168
Okay.

1:13:51.168 --> 1:13:54.378
A typewritten confession was sent
<i>to the Riverside Press Enterprise</i>

1:13:54.378 --> 1:13:57.252
on November 29th,
a month after Bates's murder.

1:13:57.252 --> 1:13:58.672
They ran it.

1:14:00.924 --> 1:14:03.714
"I'm not sick. I am insane.
But that will not stop the game.

1:14:03.714 --> 1:14:06.000
"This letter should be published
for all to read."

1:14:06.000 --> 1:14:07.420
He wants to be published.
He calls it a game.

1:14:07.420 --> 1:14:08.882
I mean, this could be our boy.

1:14:08.882 --> 1:14:12.294
Six months later, the police,
the girl's father, and the paper,

1:14:12.294 --> 1:14:14.252
they all received these.

1:14:19.084 --> 1:14:20.924
Double postage, just like Zodiac.

1:14:22.462 --> 1:14:25.462
These are what Sherwood Morrill
matched the Zodiac letters?

1:14:25.462 --> 1:14:27.588
These and the desktop. Don.

1:14:27.588 --> 1:14:31.924
This was found a couple of months later
by a janitor in RCC storage.

1:14:40.882 --> 1:14:43.504
Sherwood got
a handwriting match off wood?

1:14:45.378 --> 1:14:47.756
Who etches in their own handwriting?

1:14:47.756 --> 1:14:49.000
To be honest with you,

1:14:49.000 --> 1:14:51.462
our letters and your letters,
I don't see it.

1:14:51.462 --> 1:14:54.126
How did Paul Avery
get his hands on the exemplars?

1:14:54.126 --> 1:14:55.588
I gave them to him.

1:14:55.588 --> 1:14:57.546
We talked on the phone the other day
for about an hour.

1:14:57.546 --> 1:14:59.126
And I told him you were gonna be here.

1:14:59.126 --> 1:15:00.882
-You told him we were meeting?
-Yeah.

1:15:00.882 --> 1:15:03.168
I also told him
we don't think this is Zodiac.

1:15:03.168 --> 1:15:05.336
Okay, wait a minute.

1:15:05.336 --> 1:15:08.504
-You don't think this is Zodiac?
-We got a guy we like for it.

1:15:08.504 --> 1:15:10.168
We don't have enough
to pin it on him yet,

1:15:10.168 --> 1:15:11.504
but we're pretty sure it's him.

1:15:11.504 --> 1:15:14.504
If you don't think this is Zodiac,
then why give anything to Avery?

1:15:14.504 --> 1:15:16.210
I'm trying to cooperate.

1:15:16.210 --> 1:15:19.126
Oh, that's how you cooperate?
By giving information to reporters?

1:15:19.126 --> 1:15:20.756
Look, I don't know
about the handwriting,

1:15:20.756 --> 1:15:22.084
but Sherwood says it's a match, right?

1:15:22.084 --> 1:15:24.588
So, let's just say
that your guy did Cheri Jo.

1:15:24.588 --> 1:15:25.840
He types the confession.

1:15:25.840 --> 1:15:29.084
Zodiac reads it in the paper,
and he writes a letter taking credit for it.

1:15:29.084 --> 1:15:30.714
Now, that's something he's done before.

1:15:30.714 --> 1:15:33.420
Look, now you have everything we have.

1:15:33.420 --> 1:15:36.798
But, in my opinion,
you guys came south for nothing.

1:15:36.798 --> 1:15:39.000
FUBAR, gentlemen, FUBAR.

1:15:39.000 --> 1:15:41.840
I don't care what he says.
This still could be Z.

1:15:41.840 --> 1:15:45.168
The problem is
the entire state already thinks it is.

1:15:45.168 --> 1:15:48.546
Well, there's your press agent.
Talk to him about it.

1:15:51.042 --> 1:15:53.042
I come in peace.
I don't want any trouble.

1:15:53.042 --> 1:15:55.126
I really don't want to talk to you
right now, Paul. Not now.

1:15:55.126 --> 1:15:59.168
-Just trying to do my job.
-Oh, really? Well, now I can't do mine.

1:15:59.168 --> 1:16:01.294
We're already screwed with
the amount of tips we got on this thing,

1:16:01.294 --> 1:16:03.084
and you just freaked out the entire state.

1:16:03.126 --> 1:16:06.504
I have got Napa, Vallejo, and DOJ
looking at me sideways

1:16:06.504 --> 1:16:09.420
and Riverside's telling me
I'm on a snipe hunt!

1:16:09.420 --> 1:16:12.168
Jesus. Hey, Cheri Jo Bates was a gift.
I gave that to you.

1:16:12.168 --> 1:16:13.840
You and Armstrong
never would have found her.

1:16:13.840 --> 1:16:16.168
This may not be Zodiac.
Does that matter to you?

1:16:16.168 --> 1:16:17.630
-What if it is?
-Does it matter that Riverside may not

1:16:17.630 --> 1:16:19.798
be able to make a case
against their suspect because of you?

1:16:19.798 --> 1:16:21.798
Tell it to Sherwood.
I'm out here, beating the bushes,

1:16:21.798 --> 1:16:23.462
trying to draw him out.
We're in this together.

1:16:23.462 --> 1:16:24.924
No, we're not in anything together, Paul,

1:16:24.924 --> 1:16:26.882
because I'm not interested
in upping my circulation.

1:16:26.882 --> 1:16:29.882
Oh, boy. He wrote me.
He threatened my life.

1:16:29.882 --> 1:16:31.588
Hey, Bullitt!

1:16:31.588 --> 1:16:35.546
Been a year-and-a-half,
you gonna catch this fucking guy or not?

1:16:37.672 --> 1:16:40.126
-Go fuck yourself.
-Happily.

1:16:40.126 --> 1:16:42.168
You should have called me, Paul.

1:16:47.714 --> 1:16:48.966
Thank you.

1:17:02.210 --> 1:17:04.042
-Did you see this?
-Unfortunately, yes.

1:17:04.042 --> 1:17:06.714
Here comes every lunatic in California.

1:17:07.588 --> 1:17:08.966
I'm the Zodiac.

1:17:08.966 --> 1:17:10.630
And how did you kill your victims?

1:17:10.630 --> 1:17:13.378
With a gun. No, with a hammer.

1:17:13.378 --> 1:17:14.798
All I'm authorized to tell you

1:17:14.798 --> 1:17:16.462
is that he's still under
government employment.

1:17:16.462 --> 1:17:19.630
-And who authorized you to tell me this?
-That's all I'm authorized to say.

1:17:19.630 --> 1:17:21.840
<i>Only a little rat bastard like Andre</i>

1:17:21.840 --> 1:17:24.504
could have done something
like cut off all the victims' hands.

1:17:24.504 --> 1:17:27.000
Zodiac didn't cut off
any of the victims' hands.

1:17:27.000 --> 1:17:28.840
-Are you sure?
-Yes, sir.

1:17:28.840 --> 1:17:31.462
Travis and I worked here
side by side for 10 years.

1:17:31.462 --> 1:17:35.630
His foot gets crushed in an accident
and the killings begin.

1:17:35.630 --> 1:17:37.252
-Coincidence?
-I don't know.

1:17:37.252 --> 1:17:39.126
You're a cop, man. Do the math.

1:17:43.504 --> 1:17:46.840
Have you considered
the killer might be Paul Avery?

1:17:46.840 --> 1:17:48.042
Frequently.

1:17:48.630 --> 1:17:50.000
He was drinking Coors,
getting a load on.

1:17:50.546 --> 1:17:54.294
Starts talking about hunting people.
Like that book.

1:17:54.294 --> 1:17:56.546
Says how you can put a light
at the end of a gun

1:17:56.546 --> 1:17:58.168
to use as a sight in the dark.

1:17:58.168 --> 1:18:00.042
-He said that?
-Yeah.

1:18:00.042 --> 1:18:02.966
So I asked him,
"How would you get away with it?"

1:18:03.210 --> 1:18:05.042
And he said, "It would be easy

1:18:05.042 --> 1:18:07.546
"'cause there'd be no real motive
to the thing."

1:18:07.546 --> 1:18:09.546
Then he said he'd write letters
to the police

1:18:09.546 --> 1:18:11.420
and call himself Zodiac
to mess with them.

1:18:11.420 --> 1:18:13.126
Leigh liked messing with people.

1:18:13.126 --> 1:18:16.252
-You're positive he said "Zodiac"?
-Yeah.

1:18:16.252 --> 1:18:19.462
I thought it was a stupid name.
So I told him.

1:18:19.462 --> 1:18:22.966
He got up all upset and said,
"I don't care what you think.

1:18:22.966 --> 1:18:25.714
"I've thought about it a long time
and that's the name I'm gonna use."

1:18:25.714 --> 1:18:29.168
Did you feel like he'd been
thinking about it a long time?

1:18:29.168 --> 1:18:32.504
He was raw about losing his job
at the school.

1:18:32.504 --> 1:18:35.588
He talked about shooting out
the tires of a school bus

1:18:35.588 --> 1:18:38.084
and picking off the little darlings.

1:18:38.084 --> 1:18:42.252
-He actually used those words?
-That's what made me remember.

1:18:42.252 --> 1:18:44.798
Afterwards, I told my wife
I didn't wanna see him again.

1:18:44.798 --> 1:18:46.630
And I haven't since.

1:18:46.630 --> 1:18:49.252
Other thing is, Leigh's into skin diving.

1:18:49.252 --> 1:18:51.420
I know he's been up to that lake
a bunch of times.

1:18:51.420 --> 1:18:53.882
Lake Berryessa?
Did you ever go with him?

1:18:53.882 --> 1:18:57.966
Couple times. We went fishing
by Putah Creek near there.

1:18:57.966 --> 1:18:59.504
Tell him when you put it together.

1:18:59.504 --> 1:19:04.336
About a year ago, in the paper,
there was a story about the Zodiac.

1:19:04.336 --> 1:19:07.546
And it all comes back.
I tried to call the local cops.

1:19:07.546 --> 1:19:09.210
They blew him off.
Thought he was a nut.

1:19:09.210 --> 1:19:13.126
And you're sure
the conversation you had about Zodiac

1:19:13.126 --> 1:19:17.000
took place on January 1st, 1968?

1:19:17.000 --> 1:19:18.840
It couldn't have been any later.

1:19:18.840 --> 1:19:21.756
I started a new job in L.A.
on January 20th.

1:19:22.252 --> 1:19:23.840
I had to move.

1:19:23.840 --> 1:19:26.420
<i>-This is my problem. This guy...</i>
<i>-Arthur Leigh Allen?</i>

1:19:26.420 --> 1:19:29.126
This guy, Leigh,
just lays out his entire evil plan

1:19:29.126 --> 1:19:30.714
to a fishing buddy on New Year's Day?

1:19:30.714 --> 1:19:33.630
I don't know.
He's angry, he's been drinking,

1:19:33.630 --> 1:19:35.840
been thinking about it for a while.
I can buy that.

1:19:35.840 --> 1:19:38.294
So why didn't Cheney
contact us sooner?

1:19:38.294 --> 1:19:39.840
I checked. He did.

1:19:39.840 --> 1:19:42.924
First recorded contact
with the police department about Allen

1:19:42.924 --> 1:19:45.840
was in Pomona. January 10th, 1970.

1:19:45.840 --> 1:19:47.042
He just got lost in the shuffle.

1:19:47.042 --> 1:19:48.798
Did Cheney have anything
against Allen?

1:19:48.798 --> 1:19:50.210
Did Allen screw his wife or anything?

1:19:50.210 --> 1:19:52.000
We're gonna do
a full background check.

1:19:52.000 --> 1:19:54.714
But I got to tell you, I like this guy.

1:19:55.714 --> 1:19:57.630
So, let's pull
some handwriting samples.

1:19:59.336 --> 1:20:02.336
Hi. I talked to Sherwood.
He got the samples.

1:20:02.336 --> 1:20:04.294
-What are you having?
-BLT.

1:20:06.924 --> 1:20:09.546
So, the check stubs are a wash.
There's not enough handwriting.

1:20:09.546 --> 1:20:12.168
The application's got more,
but it doesn't look like Z's,

1:20:12.168 --> 1:20:14.588
so he can't rule him in.
But he can't rule him out, either.

1:20:14.588 --> 1:20:17.504
-Well, that's vague.
-He needs more samples.

1:20:18.546 --> 1:20:20.672
Also, our guy is a pervert.

1:20:21.714 --> 1:20:23.672
When Mel got the application
from Valley Springs,

1:20:23.672 --> 1:20:26.042
they told him that
Allen had been fired for touching kids.

1:20:26.042 --> 1:20:28.210
-Touching?
-Polite euphemism.

1:20:29.840 --> 1:20:33.084
-So what do you want to do?
-Make some phone calls.

1:20:33.084 --> 1:20:35.798
-Are you done with the fries?
-Go ahead.

1:20:35.798 --> 1:20:37.336
<i>Did you and Mr. Cheney have a chance</i>

1:20:37.336 --> 1:20:39.672
<i>to look at the copies</i>
<i>of the Zodiac letters we sent you?</i>

1:20:39.672 --> 1:20:42.462
Yeah.
Some of this stuff is pretty creepy.

1:20:42.462 --> 1:20:45.588
<i>-Yeah, we know that.</i>
-I mean, creepy like Leigh.

1:20:45.924 --> 1:20:48.546
He misspells words like that.
He thinks it's funny.

1:20:48.546 --> 1:20:50.420
What about the handwriting?

1:20:50.420 --> 1:20:53.462
<i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Don't you have experts for that stuff?</i>

1:20:53.462 --> 1:20:56.672
Our man at Questioned Documents
says it's inconclusive.

1:20:56.672 --> 1:20:58.588
Maybe he did it with his other hand.

1:20:58.588 --> 1:20:59.966
<i>The letters are a little too neat</i>

1:20:59.966 --> 1:21:02.462
<i>for someone to have written</i>
<i>with the wrong hand.</i>

1:21:02.462 --> 1:21:04.294
But not for Leigh, right.

1:21:04.294 --> 1:21:06.294
-What do you mean?
<i>-He's ambidextrous.</i>

1:21:06.294 --> 1:21:09.798
<i>He can write with either hand.</i>
<i>Didn't you guys know that?</i>

1:21:09.798 --> 1:21:12.714
In everyday life, Allen uses his left hand.

1:21:12.714 --> 1:21:15.252
Job applications,
letters to friends, et cetera.

1:21:15.252 --> 1:21:18.000
But he writes the Zodiac letters
with his right hand

1:21:18.000 --> 1:21:21.798
producing a different handwriting
that he can't be linked to.

1:21:22.210 --> 1:21:23.672
We got to see this guy, Chief.

1:21:23.672 --> 1:21:24.966
-Where is he?
-Vallejo.

1:21:24.966 --> 1:21:28.126
He works at Union Oil in Pinole.
His brother's up there, too.

1:21:28.126 --> 1:21:29.672
See them both.

1:21:29.672 --> 1:21:32.252
Make sure you call Mulanax.
It is his backyard.

1:21:32.252 --> 1:21:35.504
Oh, right, because that
worked so well for us in Riverside.

1:21:35.504 --> 1:21:38.084
Cooperation, that's us, at all costs.

1:21:47.672 --> 1:21:51.756
You can talk to him in here.
Coke machine's busted, by the way.

1:21:52.882 --> 1:21:54.882
I'll go get him for you.

1:21:56.336 --> 1:21:58.546
So how do you guys wanna do this?

1:21:58.546 --> 1:22:02.294
Well, Bill talked to the informants.
He leads, we follow?

1:22:02.294 --> 1:22:03.924
It's okay by me.

1:22:17.798 --> 1:22:20.504
Mr. Allen, I'm Inspector Bill Armstrong.

1:22:20.504 --> 1:22:23.504
This is Inspector Dave Toschi
and Sergeant Jack Mulanax.

1:22:23.504 --> 1:22:27.966
We're investigating the Zodiac murders
in San Francisco and Vallejo.

1:22:27.966 --> 1:22:29.588
Please, sit down.

1:22:38.420 --> 1:22:41.000
The informant notified us
that you made certain statements

1:22:41.000 --> 1:22:43.672
11 months prior
to the first Zodiac murder.

1:22:43.672 --> 1:22:46.798
If they're true,
they're quite incriminating.

1:22:46.798 --> 1:22:49.126
Do you recall
having any such conversation?

1:22:49.126 --> 1:22:50.336
-No.
-Have you ever read

1:22:50.336 --> 1:22:52.420
or heard anything about the Zodiac?

1:22:52.420 --> 1:22:53.756
When it was first in the paper.

1:22:53.756 --> 1:22:55.924
But I didn't follow it
after those first reports.

1:22:55.924 --> 1:22:58.462
-Why not?
-Too morbid. I...

1:22:59.420 --> 1:23:02.336
I told all this to the other officer.

1:23:02.336 --> 1:23:04.840
-Which other officer?
-From Vallejo.

1:23:06.210 --> 1:23:07.756
Do you remember his name?

1:23:07.756 --> 1:23:11.588
No, but it was right after
the murder at the lake.

1:23:11.588 --> 1:23:14.042
And what did you tell this officer?

1:23:15.630 --> 1:23:19.966
I told him that I'd gone to Salt Point
that weekend to skin dive.

1:23:19.966 --> 1:23:22.798
That I was alone
but I met a couple there.

1:23:23.966 --> 1:23:26.168
I have their names at home
if you want them.

1:23:26.168 --> 1:23:27.924
That would be great, Arthur.

1:23:27.924 --> 1:23:29.840
-Leigh.
-What?

1:23:30.672 --> 1:23:33.210
Leigh. Nobody calls me Arthur.

1:23:34.966 --> 1:23:38.462
Also, that day when I came home,
my neighbor saw me.

1:23:38.462 --> 1:23:42.336
It was around 4:00.
But I forgot to tell the other officer that.

1:23:42.336 --> 1:23:44.546
-Neighbor's name?
-Bill White.

1:23:46.336 --> 1:23:48.210
He died a week or so afterwards.

1:23:48.210 --> 1:23:51.630
Heart attack.
So I didn't think to call to follow up.

1:23:53.798 --> 1:23:55.966
The knives I had in my car
with the blood on them,

1:23:55.966 --> 1:23:59.546
that blood came from a chicken
that I killed for dinner.

1:24:02.336 --> 1:24:05.210
-What?
-I had knives in my car that weekend.

1:24:05.210 --> 1:24:09.504
Maybe Bill saw them
and called the other officer on me.

1:24:10.126 --> 1:24:13.294
Well, we'll be checking in on that.

1:24:13.294 --> 1:24:14.840
Well, let me ask you something else.

1:24:14.840 --> 1:24:18.798
Were you ever in Southern California
at any time in 1966?

1:24:19.798 --> 1:24:22.336
-Is this about the Riverside killing?
-Yes.

1:24:23.420 --> 1:24:25.798
Well, I guess I was there
around that time.

1:24:25.798 --> 1:24:29.126
I used to go down there a lot.
I like the auto races.

1:24:33.462 --> 1:24:36.000
Informant says that
you're ambidextrous?

1:24:36.000 --> 1:24:38.000
No, that's untrue.

1:24:38.000 --> 1:24:40.336
You can't write with both hands?

1:24:41.504 --> 1:24:44.672
My teachers tried to make me
when I was a kid, but I couldn't.

1:24:44.672 --> 1:24:46.882
I'm left-handed.

1:24:46.882 --> 1:24:51.042
He also said that you made statements
about killing school children.

1:24:51.756 --> 1:24:53.336
That is...

1:24:53.336 --> 1:24:56.714
That is horrible. That is...
That's a horrible thing to say.

1:24:56.714 --> 1:25:00.000
So, you weren't angry
about being fired from Valley Springs

1:25:00.000 --> 1:25:02.252
for touching your students?

1:25:11.504 --> 1:25:13.210
I'm not the Zodiac.

1:25:14.168 --> 1:25:17.168
And if I was, I certainly wouldn't tell you.

1:25:19.378 --> 1:25:21.210
That's a nice watch.

1:25:23.042 --> 1:25:24.168
Thank you.

1:25:24.168 --> 1:25:25.336
May I see it?

1:25:25.336 --> 1:25:25.630
May I see it?

1:25:27.546 --> 1:25:29.000
May I see it?

1:25:40.840 --> 1:25:41.924
Where'd you get it?

1:25:42.084 --> 1:25:44.924
It was Christmas gift
from my mother two years ago.

1:25:44.924 --> 1:25:47.168
That's very sweet.

1:25:47.168 --> 1:25:49.882
So, tell me something, Arthur.

1:25:49.882 --> 1:25:51.000
You don't remember anyone

1:25:51.000 --> 1:25:54.882
you might have had a conversation with
regarding the Zodiac?

1:25:56.000 --> 1:26:01.420
Maybe Ted Kidder or Phil Tucker
at Vallejo Recreation.

1:26:02.714 --> 1:26:04.630
But I couldn't be positive.

1:26:04.630 --> 1:26:06.798
I used to work there when...

1:26:10.462 --> 1:26:12.546
<i>The Most Dangerous Game.</i>

1:26:13.840 --> 1:26:15.000
What?

1:26:15.000 --> 1:26:18.294
<i>The Most Dangerous Game.</i>
That's why you're here, isn't it?

1:26:18.294 --> 1:26:20.126
It was my favorite book in high school.

1:26:20.126 --> 1:26:23.714
It's about this man who waits for people
to get shipwrecked on this island.

1:26:23.714 --> 1:26:25.210
Because he was
tired of hunting animals,

1:26:25.210 --> 1:26:26.882
he hunted the people for the challenge.

1:26:26.882 --> 1:26:31.126
And man is the most
dangerous animal of all?

1:26:31.126 --> 1:26:33.672
That's the whole point of the story.

1:26:34.336 --> 1:26:35.714
Great book.

1:26:36.924 --> 1:26:39.588
Or, at least, that's what I told Phil.

1:26:45.168 --> 1:26:46.420
May I go?

1:26:50.000 --> 1:26:51.126
Sure.

1:26:55.966 --> 1:27:00.336
-Thanks for your time.
-I'm willing to help in any way possible.

1:27:00.336 --> 1:27:02.504
I look forward to the day

1:27:02.504 --> 1:27:06.000
when police officers
are no longer referred to as pigs.

1:27:06.966 --> 1:27:08.168
Thanks.

1:27:09.252 --> 1:27:10.924
We'll be in touch.

1:27:22.672 --> 1:27:26.882
So does anyone think this suspect
warrants further investigation?

1:27:26.882 --> 1:27:29.882
These are copies of some
of the Zodiac letters that were sent.

1:27:30.378 --> 1:27:33.798
We'd like you to take a look at them.

1:27:33.798 --> 1:27:35.756
You think my brother's the Zodiac.

1:27:35.756 --> 1:27:37.840
Well, we're looking at him.

1:27:37.840 --> 1:27:39.294
Are you going to arrest him?

1:27:39.294 --> 1:27:43.336
Mrs. Allen, we don't arrest people
just because we're interested in them.

1:27:43.336 --> 1:27:44.882
Well, Leigh's always been troubled.

1:27:44.882 --> 1:27:47.084
Is it true about the children?

1:27:47.630 --> 1:27:49.168
Unfortunately.

1:27:49.168 --> 1:27:51.882
We don't see him much anymore
since we found out.

1:27:51.882 --> 1:27:54.000
What are your feelings
about Don Cheney?

1:27:54.000 --> 1:27:56.420
Don Cheney? My old roommate?

1:27:56.420 --> 1:27:59.504
-Was he the one who contacted you?
-That's confidential.

1:27:59.504 --> 1:28:01.126
Well, Don's a very reliable guy.

1:28:01.126 --> 1:28:04.294
If he were to tell you something,
I'd believe it to be true.

1:28:04.294 --> 1:28:05.546
-This one.
-What about it?

1:28:05.546 --> 1:28:07.798
Here, where he spells
"Christmas" with two "S's."

1:28:07.798 --> 1:28:09.840
We got a Christmas card from Leigh
a couple years ago.

1:28:09.840 --> 1:28:12.966
He spelled it the exact same way.
Christ-mass.

1:28:12.966 --> 1:28:15.798
-Would you still have that?
-I can look for it.

1:28:15.798 --> 1:28:17.924
Thank you. That'd be great.

1:28:19.042 --> 1:28:21.168
Is there anything else
we can do to help?

1:28:21.168 --> 1:28:22.924
<i>The brother said</i>
<i>he would search Leigh's apartment</i>

1:28:22.924 --> 1:28:24.252
next time he went out of town.

1:28:24.252 --> 1:28:26.588
-That gets you around a warrant.
-For the time being.

1:28:26.588 --> 1:28:29.924
If we do find something,
Mulanax will go to the DA in Vallejo,

1:28:29.924 --> 1:28:31.756
and we could search the place properly.

1:28:31.756 --> 1:28:33.336
Now I got a chance to talk to the cop

1:28:33.336 --> 1:28:36.294
who interviewed Leigh Allen
two days after the Berryessa murders.

1:28:36.294 --> 1:28:38.084
Doesn't remember how he got onto him,

1:28:38.084 --> 1:28:41.210
but didn't think he looked like a killer
so he didn't like him for Z.

1:28:41.210 --> 1:28:44.126
-But you do?
-I wish I could've taken the guy in there.

1:28:44.126 --> 1:28:47.168
Take it slow, Dave.
Try and find more stuff for Sherwood.

1:28:47.168 --> 1:28:49.294
A match'll get us farther
on the warrants.

1:28:49.294 --> 1:28:52.504
-Avery's on two.
-Tell him to screw.

1:28:52.504 --> 1:28:56.840
You want me to communicate that
verbatim or can I spice it up a little?

1:29:06.630 --> 1:29:08.084
Christ, kid.

1:29:09.714 --> 1:29:10.756
Yeah.

1:29:10.756 --> 1:29:13.168
-Paul, I've been thinking...
-Oh, God save us all.

1:29:13.168 --> 1:29:14.630
The letter to Melvin Belli

1:29:14.630 --> 1:29:17.672
was sent exactly one year
after the Lake Herman Road murder.

1:29:17.672 --> 1:29:19.504
And the one to Cheri Jo Bates' father

1:29:19.504 --> 1:29:21.966
was sent exactly six months
after her death.

1:29:21.966 --> 1:29:24.378
-She was killed a day before Halloween.
-Yeah.

1:29:24.378 --> 1:29:25.966
And you received a Halloween card...

1:29:25.966 --> 1:29:28.672
You know, these are all fascinating
pieces of news, Robert,

1:29:28.672 --> 1:29:30.714
it's a bit early in the day.

1:29:30.714 --> 1:29:33.588
Paul, it's 11:00 and we missed Editorial.

1:29:38.168 --> 1:29:40.294
-I'm sorry. I didn't mean to wake you up.
-No, no, no.

1:29:40.294 --> 1:29:41.504
-I just thought that...
-No, no, no.

1:29:47.126 --> 1:29:49.504
This suspect is not your Zodiac.

1:29:51.588 --> 1:29:54.210
This sample matches the canceled
checks and the application?

1:29:54.210 --> 1:29:55.294
Perfectly.

1:29:55.294 --> 1:29:58.630
So we've just retested the left hand.
I mean, we know he's ambidextrous.

1:29:58.630 --> 1:30:01.966
In 38 years, I've never seen anyone
that ambidextrous.

1:30:01.966 --> 1:30:04.462
Both hands would have commonalities.

1:30:04.798 --> 1:30:06.126
I'm sorry.

1:30:06.588 --> 1:30:08.336
Just not gonna work.

1:30:10.252 --> 1:30:12.756
<i>-Homicide, Toschi.</i>
-Dave, it's Jack Mulanax.

1:30:12.756 --> 1:30:15.000
Hey. Mulanax. Yeah.

1:30:15.000 --> 1:30:16.504
<i>We struck out with the judge.</i>

1:30:16.504 --> 1:30:18.210
<i>He won't sign off on a warrant</i>
<i>for Allen's house.</i>

1:30:18.210 --> 1:30:20.378
-Why not?
-Said it wasn't enough.

1:30:20.378 --> 1:30:22.798
Now, unless we bring him a handwriting
match or some evidence that...

1:30:22.798 --> 1:30:25.252
How are we gonna get evidence
if we can't toss the house?

1:30:25.252 --> 1:30:26.756
<i>I don't know.</i>

1:30:27.252 --> 1:30:30.210
-I truly am sorry.
<i>-No, no. Thank you, Jack.</i>

1:30:32.084 --> 1:30:33.252
What do you wanna do?

1:30:33.252 --> 1:30:34.672
Don't know what I can do
without Vallejo.

1:30:34.672 --> 1:30:37.630
We need Allen's right hand.
We can't get it without a warrant.

1:30:37.630 --> 1:30:39.798
Are there other guys
you should be looking at?

1:30:39.840 --> 1:30:41.840
Only, what?

1:30:41.840 --> 1:30:43.840
Twenty-three hundred?

1:30:43.840 --> 1:30:45.210
Okay, then.

1:30:48.378 --> 1:30:49.714
Okay, then.

1:31:17.630 --> 1:31:20.378
Paul, you wrote the Justice Department

1:31:20.378 --> 1:31:23.756
asking to be put in charge
of the Zodiac investigation?

1:31:25.756 --> 1:31:27.756
I merely suggested...

1:31:27.756 --> 1:31:29.042
On our letterhead?

1:31:29.084 --> 1:31:31.210
...that those with intimate knowledge
of the case

1:31:31.210 --> 1:31:33.252
create an information clearinghouse

1:31:33.252 --> 1:31:35.462
to promote an exchange
and free flow of ideas.

1:31:35.462 --> 1:31:38.588
-And that you run it.
-Well, who better than me?

1:31:39.630 --> 1:31:41.168
The marked man.

1:31:41.882 --> 1:31:43.924
Paul, if you want to work here,
I need three things.

1:31:43.924 --> 1:31:45.462
One, stop boozing.

1:31:45.504 --> 1:31:48.756
Two, stop doing
whatever else it is you're doing.

1:31:48.756 --> 1:31:52.336
And three, cut this nonsense out.

1:31:52.336 --> 1:31:55.546
Sweetest of Templetons, if at any time

1:31:55.546 --> 1:32:00.840
you feel my excellent work is no longer
in step with this trashy provincial rag,

1:32:00.840 --> 1:32:02.588
I'll more than happily...

1:32:02.588 --> 1:32:06.168
More than happily
decamp for greener pastures.

1:32:06.168 --> 1:32:07.798
Paul, I mean it!

1:32:17.966 --> 1:32:19.966
-Paul?
-Yep.

1:32:19.966 --> 1:32:23.168
-What was that?
-An editorial tête-à-tête.

1:32:24.336 --> 1:32:26.504
-Wanna grab a drink?
-It's 10:00 in the morning.

1:32:26.504 --> 1:32:28.336
Late breakfast?

1:32:29.378 --> 1:32:31.504
-Early lunch, or...
-Paul.

1:32:33.966 --> 1:32:35.420
Are you okay?

1:32:36.252 --> 1:32:37.336
No.

1:32:40.756 --> 1:32:42.588
Thank you for asking.

1:32:44.798 --> 1:32:47.000
Shorty! Let's go out for one.

1:32:47.000 --> 1:32:49.042
Paul, where are you going?

1:32:51.084 --> 1:32:52.672
<i>So, you moved off my brother-in-law?</i>

1:32:53.672 --> 1:32:55.630
We couldn't get a warrant.

1:32:57.252 --> 1:33:00.798
Last year we arranged for Leigh
to get help from a social worker.

1:33:00.798 --> 1:33:02.546
He only went twice.

1:33:02.546 --> 1:33:05.588
We saw him recently for
the first time in nine months.

1:33:05.588 --> 1:33:08.840
My mother-in-law brought him by
to see the new baby.

1:33:08.840 --> 1:33:12.252
After he left,
I went to see that social worker.

1:33:12.252 --> 1:33:15.672
He couldn't talk about a former patient,
so I just asked him straight out

1:33:15.672 --> 1:33:17.924
if he thought Leigh
was capable of killing people.

1:33:17.966 --> 1:33:21.210
-Because of patient confidentiality...
-The man said yes.

1:33:23.000 --> 1:33:25.294
Why hadn't you seen him
in nine months?

1:33:25.294 --> 1:33:27.294
He's going to school in Santa Rosa.

1:33:27.294 --> 1:33:30.714
-Santa Rosa? Where is he living?
-In his trailer.

1:33:30.714 --> 1:33:32.840
-In Santa Rosa?
-Sonoma County.

1:33:32.840 --> 1:33:35.168
We wouldn't have to go
through the Vallejo DA.

1:33:35.168 --> 1:33:36.756
It's been 11 months
since you talked to this guy,

1:33:36.756 --> 1:33:38.378
and now you wanna search his trailer?

1:33:38.378 --> 1:33:40.252
If we find something, great.

1:33:40.252 --> 1:33:43.546
If not, we get his prints and
handwriting samples from both hands.

1:33:43.546 --> 1:33:45.924
I thought Sherwood shut you down.

1:33:46.630 --> 1:33:49.126
What if I can get a second opinion?

1:33:50.252 --> 1:33:52.378
I don't wanna step on Sherwood's toes.
He trained me at this.

1:33:52.378 --> 1:33:55.252
Terry, all I need to know
is if the suspect is ambidextrous.

1:33:55.252 --> 1:33:59.252
Could he possibly have written
those letters with his other hand?

1:34:00.924 --> 1:34:02.378
Between you and me?

1:34:02.378 --> 1:34:05.840
Because there are differing
schools of thought on this.

1:34:07.000 --> 1:34:11.546
Get the samples of his other hand.
If he's the Zodiac, you'll get a match.

1:34:11.546 --> 1:34:14.210
<i>That's the current thinking,</i>
<i>according to Terry Pascoe.</i>

1:34:14.210 --> 1:34:17.588
Meanwhile, I spoke to a psychologist
who'd be willing to testify

1:34:17.588 --> 1:34:20.672
that someone who undergoes
a personality change like Zodiac

1:34:20.672 --> 1:34:23.714
would manifest it physically,
altering his handwriting.

1:34:23.714 --> 1:34:27.420
Which is why Sherwood couldn't
get a match from Allen's samples.

1:34:27.420 --> 1:34:29.756
We got Terry Pascoe,
this psychology guy,

1:34:29.756 --> 1:34:31.168
coupled with Cheney...

1:34:31.168 --> 1:34:32.756
It could be enough for a warrant.

1:34:32.756 --> 1:34:33.924
Get Cheney on the record.

1:34:34.168 --> 1:34:37.252
"And that he would call himself Zodiac."

1:34:38.336 --> 1:34:39.462
Yes.

1:34:39.462 --> 1:34:43.126
And you're willing to swear
to this, under oath, in Superior Court?

1:34:43.126 --> 1:34:44.630
Without any hesitation.

1:34:44.630 --> 1:34:46.882
Thank you very much, Mr. Cheney.
Thank you very much for your time.

1:34:46.882 --> 1:34:48.000
Thank you.

1:34:48.000 --> 1:34:49.924
Suspect is Arthur Leigh Allen.

1:34:49.924 --> 1:34:53.756
Lives in Sunset Trailer Court
in Santa Rosa, California.

1:34:53.756 --> 1:34:55.420
Physical description.

1:34:55.420 --> 1:34:57.756
Allen is similar in height,
weight and build

1:34:57.756 --> 1:35:00.966
to a man seen at Lake Berryessa
on the day of the stabbings.

1:35:00.966 --> 1:35:03.840
<i>I understand he doesn't look</i>
<i>much like the San Francisco composite.</i>

1:35:03.840 --> 1:35:05.462
True. Height and weight are sketchy,

1:35:05.504 --> 1:35:07.798
but lumbering Caucasian
with a crew cut is right on.

1:35:07.798 --> 1:35:10.168
We never had much confidence
in the composite from the kids.

1:35:10.168 --> 1:35:12.294
The patrolman
who say Zodiac that night

1:35:12.294 --> 1:35:13.840
said he didn't look much like the sketch.

1:35:13.882 --> 1:35:15.420
Military boot prints.

1:35:15.420 --> 1:35:18.252
Allen was in the Navy.
Wears a size 10-and-a-half.

1:35:18.252 --> 1:35:20.798
Same size as the prints
found at Berryessa.

1:35:20.798 --> 1:35:22.588
<i>What about gun?</i>

1:35:22.588 --> 1:35:27.252
Cheney says Allen owns several
firearms. We'll list them in the warrant.

1:35:27.252 --> 1:35:30.126
<i>-And the ciphers.</i>
-Could be code training in the Navy,

1:35:30.126 --> 1:35:32.966
and people have seen Allen
with ciphers in the past.

1:35:32.966 --> 1:35:34.084
<i>Really? Who?</i>

1:35:34.084 --> 1:35:36.966
That would be his sister-in-law
and a man named Phil Tucker

1:35:36.966 --> 1:35:39.378
that he worked with
at a public pool in Vallejo.

1:35:39.378 --> 1:35:42.966
And Phil Tucker told us about
a conversation that he had with Allen

1:35:42.966 --> 1:35:45.756
about how to attach a flashlight
to the barrel of a gun.

1:35:45.756 --> 1:35:49.084
That gives us two sources
on the ciphers and two on the flashlight.

1:35:49.084 --> 1:35:51.210
<i>What about his threats on children?</i>

1:35:51.210 --> 1:35:53.042
Suspect worked for elementary schools

1:35:53.042 --> 1:35:56.378
and was fired for molestation
in March, April '68.

1:35:56.378 --> 1:35:59.084
-Could give him motive.
-At the very least, it's home turf.

1:35:59.084 --> 1:36:01.252
He'd have knowledge of bus routes,

1:36:01.252 --> 1:36:03.798
which the two major threats
centered around.

1:36:03.798 --> 1:36:05.546
<i>What about the bomb?</i>

1:36:06.966 --> 1:36:09.000
Allen works as a chemist.

1:36:09.000 --> 1:36:10.546
Take him through the geography.

1:36:10.546 --> 1:36:12.126
Vallejo murders.

1:36:12.126 --> 1:36:15.714
Allen lives in Vallejo
with his mother in her basement.

1:36:15.714 --> 1:36:19.000
Berryessa murder. On the day
that the two kids were stabbed

1:36:19.000 --> 1:36:21.756
his neighbor saw bloody knives
in his truck

1:36:21.756 --> 1:36:24.756
which he claimed were used
to kill a chicken.

1:36:24.756 --> 1:36:26.714
<i>Does he have any alibis?</i>

1:36:26.714 --> 1:36:29.462
He claimed he did, but he's been unable
to produce the names

1:36:29.462 --> 1:36:32.840
of the couple he supposedly met
on the day of Berryessa.

1:36:32.840 --> 1:36:35.294
The bottom line is that Allen
can't alibi up on anything.

1:36:35.294 --> 1:36:37.210
Riverside, Vallejo, the lake or us.

1:36:37.210 --> 1:36:39.504
-You want to tell me about the name?
<i>-What name?</i>

1:36:39.504 --> 1:36:40.714
Zodiac.

1:36:40.714 --> 1:36:44.714
Allen wears a watch that bears
both the word and crosshair symbol.

1:36:44.714 --> 1:36:46.168
And he mentioned Zodiac to Cheney

1:36:46.168 --> 1:36:48.756
a year and a half
before it appeared in any letter.

1:36:51.924 --> 1:36:54.462
-John...
<i>-That's pretty good, guys.</i>

1:36:54.462 --> 1:36:57.462
-We think so, too.
<i>-Let's take it to a judge.</i>

1:37:17.630 --> 1:37:19.000
Mr. Allen?

1:37:19.000 --> 1:37:21.126
This is the
Santa Rosa Police Department.

1:37:21.126 --> 1:37:23.966
We have a warrant
to search your residence.

1:37:34.966 --> 1:37:36.126
Hello?

1:37:44.840 --> 1:37:47.084
I'll check with the neighbors.

1:37:48.378 --> 1:37:49.504
Close the door.

1:37:49.504 --> 1:37:52.588
Close the door,
there's rodents running around.

1:38:04.924 --> 1:38:07.546
Neighbor said he tore out of here
about a half-hour ago.

1:38:07.546 --> 1:38:11.882
-You think somebody tipped him?
-We're not leaving till he comes back.

1:38:17.714 --> 1:38:19.462
I'll check the back.

1:38:32.168 --> 1:38:33.294
Jesus.

1:38:33.294 --> 1:38:34.924
-What?
-Squirrels.

1:38:37.042 --> 1:38:39.042
Piece of work, this guy.

1:38:45.924 --> 1:38:48.714
Not one, but two blue windbreakers.

1:38:48.714 --> 1:38:52.420
-Like the Stine scene?
-We'll have those checked for blood.

1:38:52.882 --> 1:38:55.798
And a pair of black gloves.

1:38:57.126 --> 1:39:00.504
Men's seven,
just like the ones we found in the cab.

1:39:00.504 --> 1:39:03.168
Well, he's got the same size shoes
and gloves as Z.

1:39:03.168 --> 1:39:05.672
Probably just a coincidence.

1:39:05.672 --> 1:39:09.546
Dave, I got a gun.
Check that. Two guns.

1:39:10.714 --> 1:39:14.042
They're both .22s.
One automatic, one revolver.

1:39:14.042 --> 1:39:15.672
Well, that's interesting.

1:39:15.672 --> 1:39:18.924
Because he happens to have
an M-1 rifle here in the closet.

1:39:18.924 --> 1:39:21.546
For little darlings bouncing off buses.

1:39:23.000 --> 1:39:24.546
Someone's here.

1:39:31.462 --> 1:39:33.924
Hello, Arthur. Remember us?

1:39:56.462 --> 1:39:57.630
No.

1:39:57.630 --> 1:39:58.798
On the handwriting?

1:39:58.798 --> 1:40:02.420
Ballistics, no match.
Prints, no match. Writing, no match.

1:40:02.420 --> 1:40:04.252
On both hands, right?

1:40:04.252 --> 1:40:06.126
Because we got handwriting
from both his hands.

1:40:06.168 --> 1:40:07.588
And neither hand matches.

1:40:07.588 --> 1:40:09.336
Forget Sherwood.
Let's get another opinion.

1:40:09.336 --> 1:40:11.336
Fellas, he's not your guy.

1:40:18.042 --> 1:40:19.252
Damn it.

1:40:26.420 --> 1:40:27.504
Hey.

1:40:28.336 --> 1:40:30.924
What do you want? Time off?

1:40:33.126 --> 1:40:34.252
A hug?

1:40:35.126 --> 1:40:37.168
Do you know what
the worst part of this is?

1:40:37.168 --> 1:40:39.168
I can't tell if I wanted it
to be Allen so bad

1:40:39.168 --> 1:40:42.546
because I actually thought it was him,
or I just want all this to be over.

1:40:42.546 --> 1:40:44.546
It's because you thought it was him.

1:40:44.546 --> 1:40:46.084
And I did, too.

1:40:48.882 --> 1:40:50.378
You know what? Take some time off.

1:40:50.378 --> 1:40:53.756
Spend some time with your wife
and the kids.

1:40:53.756 --> 1:40:56.336
Go to Candlestick. See a movie.

